**Davey:**  Yeah, but... when I think about meeting it for the second time... I just lose it. I don't become reliable anymore. I know I've said that there's no way Roan would still be alive, but that's just me convincing myself to face the truth.

**Simon:** Daveyâ€”

**Davey:** Back then, I didn't do my job properly. I fought with Roan, pushed him away, and I suffered the consequences. We were longtime crewmates, but back then all that I could think about //wasn't// Roan, it was the whale. I didn't give a rat's ass about what would happen to him then, and because of that... he was taken away.

//[Silence.]//

**Davey:** And that's the truth. That's what scares me. The fact that I know this, all of it, and I push it away so that I can see another day is what haunts me. Simon, I'm scared. What if he's //really// alive and out there, and we manage to bring him back? What will he say to me then? Can I still be a captain, then? Do I really deserve to be his captain?

